org.safs.selenium.webdriver.lib.model

Class AbstractHierarchicalSelectable

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.safs.selenium.webdriver.lib.model.EmbeddedObject
      • org.safs.selenium.webdriver.lib.model.AbstractSelectable
        • org.safs.selenium.webdriver.lib.model.AbstractHierarchicalSelectable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IOperable, ISelectable, Supportable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractMenuSelectable, AbstractTreeSelectable

    public abstract class AbstractHierarchicalSelectable
extends AbstractSelectable
    This class represents a hierarchical selectable structure like Tree or Menu etc.
    It provides a defult implementation of #getMatchedElement(String, boolean, int)

    History:

    Jun 23, 2014 (Lei Wang) Initial release.

    • Method Detail

      • selectItem

        public void selectItem(int index,
              boolean verify,
              Keys key,
              java.awt.Point offset,
              int mouseButtonNumber)
                throws SeleniumPlusException
        Description copied from interface: ISelectable
        Try to select (single-click) the item according to the index, and then verify if the item has been really selected according to the parameter 'verify'. If the parameter key is provided, the selection will happen with that key pressed at the same time. If the parameter offset is provided, then click at offset relative to the top-left corner of view; otherwise at the center. The parameter mouseButtonNumber decides right-click or left-click.
        Note: There are maybe some callback methods associated with the item-container, but setting select index MAY NOT invoke them, in the implementation of this method we should make sure those callbacks are invoked (we can fire some events.)
        Parameters:
        index - int, the index of the item to select, it is 0-based index.
        verify - boolean, if true then verify the selection;
        key - org.openqa.selenium.Keys, it is the key to press during selection.
        for example Keys#SHIFT, or Keys#CONTROL.
        If user doesn't want any key pressed, please provide null
        offset - Point, the position relative to the up-left corner to click at
        If user provides null, then the center of the item will be used
        mouseButtonNumber - int, the mouse-button-number representing right, middle, or left button.
        it can be WDLibrary.MOUSE_BUTTON_LEFT or WDLibrary.MOUSE_BUTTON_RIGHT
        or WDLibrary.MOUSE_BUTTON_MIDDLE.
        Throws:
        SeleniumPlusException

        If user provides null, then the center of the item will be used

      • getMatchedElement

        public HierarchicalElement getMatchedElement(TextMatchingCriterion criteria)
                                      throws SeleniumPlusException
        According to the "hierarchical path" to get a Element object.
        The sub-class needs to provide an appropriate implementation of method AbstractSelectable.getContent(), on which
        this method depends. Subclass can override this method to cast the result HierarchicalElement to ist own type.
        Parameters:
        path - String, the hierarchical path, "root->node1" for example. The path should be separated by GuiObjectRecognition.DEFAULT_PATH_SEPARATOR
        Returns:
        Element, the matched Element object.
        Throws:
        SeleniumPlusException - if Element cannot be found
        See Also:
        AbstractSelectable.getContent()

      • getMatchedNode

        HierarchicalElement getMatchedNode(HierarchicalElement[] hierarchicalStructure,
                                 java.lang.String[] pathNodes,
                                 boolean partialMatch,
                                 MutableInteger matchedTimes,
                                 int expectedMatchTimes)
                             throws SeleniumPlusException
        According to a pathNodes (an array of path) and expectedMatchTimes, find the Nth-matched node in a hierarchical structure.
        Parameters:
        hierarchicalStructure - HierarchicalElement[], the hierarchical structure where to find the matched node.
        pathNodes - String[], an array of node path to match
        partialMatch - boolean, if the pathNodes contains partial string or full string to match
        matchedTimes - MutableInteger, how many times that the node-path has been found.
        expectedMatchTimes - int, the expected times that the node-path should be found.
        Returns:
        HierarchicalElement, the matched node. Sub-class may need to convert it to its own type.
        Throws:
        SeleniumPlusException

      • getMatchedNode

        HierarchicalElement getMatchedNode(HierarchicalElement[] hierarchicalStructure,
                                 java.lang.String[] pathNodes,
                                 boolean partialMatch,
                                 int[] expectedMatchTimes)
                             throws SeleniumPlusException
        According to a pathNodes (an array of path) and expectedMatchTimes (an array of int), find the matched node in a hierarchical structure.
        If at certain level, the expectedMatchedTime is not satisfied, then the search will fail and just return a null.
        Parameters:
        hierarchicalStructure - HierarchicalElement[], the hierarchical structure where to find the matched node.
        pathNodes - String[], an array of node path to match
        partialMatch - boolean, if the pathNodes contains partial string or full string to match
        expectedMatchTimes - int[], an array of int, each int value represents the expected times that the node-path should be found at its level.
        Returns:
        HierarchicalElement, the matched node. Sub-class may need to convert it to its own type.
        Throws:
        SeleniumPlusException
